<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause xmlns:xt="urn:xpressauthor:trackchanges" id="_b11c6e00-16e8-49b7-aca6-cbf5d0ba18fb" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/></meta><sptc>H7F2</sptc><title id="_9ef9b185-3672-431d-9e80-6c45fc070d01">Heating appliances</title><archive-num>2019: F2.7.2</archive-num><subclause id="_1246fcb3-c2ff-4660-8748-b68725bf3795" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_721a82e9-4c7e-4b59-bdfc-5be0a2ac1457">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A heating appliance using controlled combustion located in a building is to be installed in a way which reduces the likelihood of—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_681c1d9c-1b5a-44b6-94f1-911a7ebe1439">fire spreading beyond the appliance; and</li><li id="_2755046a-bdbf-4c5d-b064-7da5559f367d">smoke from the appliance entering the building.</li></ol></subclause></clause>